description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity for an innovative and patient focused pharmacy technician to develop into a specialist technician role while delivering a quality medicines management service as part of an established and enthusiastic medicines management team.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder should be ready for a new challenge, show initiative in supporting service improvements, be a team player and have good problem solving skills. The post will be shared between antimicrobial stewardship and medicines management 50/50.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The antimicrobial stewardship role is a brand new position at HHFT and you will have scope to develop and innovate within the post. You will contribute directly to the trust&#39;s antimicrobial stewardship agenda and be part of a growing and passionate antimicrobial stewardship team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will provide Medicines Management at ward level, be involved with medicines reconciliation, checking patients own medicines, initiating medicine supplies, providing information and advice to patients about their medicines and assisting with discharges. You will also work in the dispensary to maintain your ACPT accreditation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is open to applications from registered pharmacy technicians. Previous ward-based hospital experience and an accredited checking qualification are desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information please contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Louise Bond, Deputy Lead Medicines Management Technician&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;louise.bond1@hhft.nhs.uk 01962 824596&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jonathan Peters, Lead Antimicrobial Pharmacist&lt;/p&gt;
